岗位描述原文:
Job DescriptionMission/Position Headline:

 ● Deeply manage sales data, support decision-making to improve operational efficiency and achieve sales targets;
 ● Lead or participate in business optimization projects, drive the full project cycle with data, and promote business optimization.
Areas of Responsibilties:

 ● Maintain the end-to-end sales database to ensure data accuracy, completeness and timeliness;
 ● Design and manage data visualization solutions, optimize database logic, achieve automation of analysis reports, and improve data delivery efficiency;
 ● Respond to cross-departmental data needs, provide customized data analysis support, deliver reports and refine actionable optimization suggestions;
 ● Integrate multi-source internal data, develop and maintain robust performance tracking and forecasting models to improve the accuracy of sales forecasting and resource allocation;
 ● Lead end-to-end data support for incentive projects, align with business objectives and issue timely data alerts;
 ● Support the evaluation of external data service providers, and track service quality and delivery progress;
 ● Develop data usage guidelines, conduct tool and process training in line with business scenarios, and enhance the team’s data application capabilities;
 ● Coordinate with relevant functional team to implement the tasks from headquarters and ensure timely delivery of information or data.
 ● Perform tasks assigned by line manager.

Education and Experience

 ● 10+ years data analysis experience, proficient in end-to-end sales database management &amp; data visualization (e.g., SQL, Power BI/Tableau); medical/healthcare experience preferred.
 ● Over 3years in supporting sales operation or Business Excellence projects is a plus.
 ● Cross-departmental coordination or external data service experience is a plus.
 ● Bachelor's degree or above

